  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Manager (F&B)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead the entire food services operations and handle any operational related matters.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate and review strategies on client satisfaction pertaining to operations for all F&amp;B restaurant outlets.</li>\n  <li>Develop and direct company’s overall budget planning strategy, plans and cost saving practices.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the financial budgets and preparation of periodic financial reports / statements (for management purposes) for all F&amp;B outlets.</li>\n  <li>Supervise and work closely with Director Operations on the outlets' financial target and ensure their operating effectiveness.</li>\n  <li>Implement appropriate and efficient approaches to meet sales target.</li>\n  <li>Continue to review and assess the effectiveness and efficiency of the company’s policies, procedures, processes and identify improvement opportunities in line with the defined Business Units performance framework.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with respective F&amp;B outlet's Restaurant Manager to ensure that the deployment of manpower effectively serves the critical goals and needs.</li>\n  <li>Provide leadership and guidance to Restaurant Managers on addressing the service, organization and cost saving issues.</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain good working relationship with the customers and clients.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 4-5 years of relevant experience in managing F&amp;B outlets in a Managerial position.</li>\n  <li>Resilient and able to perform under pressure</li>\n  <li>Excellent communications and interpersonal skills.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
